<body>
    <h1>Task 20 - Technical document</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h1 local-id=3D"dab649d4065e" id=3D"Task20-Technicaldocument-1.Intr=
oduction">1. Introduction</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"3d4b142ef5fb" id=3D"Task20-Technicaldocument-1.1Purpose">1.=
1 Purpose</h2>
<p local-id=3D"cef0556d562b">This document provides a comprehensive technic=
al reference for the implementation, configuration, and validation of a sel=
f-hosted DNS server (BIND9) on an AWS EC2 instance and its comparison with =
AWS Route 53 as a managed DNS service. It describes the end-to-end setup, N=
S record delegation, DNS resolution testing, and the observed behavior when=
 switching nameserver authority between the two DNS environments.</p>
<p local-id=3D"c689ae4c1e33">This document is intended for the following au=
diences:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"273b9633156d"><strong>CTO</strong> =E2=80=93 Strategic under=
standing of managed vs self-hosted DNS trade-offs and business implications=
</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"285766a8cc99"><strong>Developers</strong> =E2=80=93 Referenc=
e for DNS record types, zone file configuration, and resolution behavior</p=
></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"c8938ea1dba6"><strong>Solution Architects</strong> =E2=80=93=
 Design guidance for DNS architecture decisions on AWS</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"35a3e935692d"><strong>DevOps Engineers</strong> =E2=80=93 St=
ep-by-step operational runbook for BIND9 setup, Route 53 configuration, and=
 dig-based validation</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"9a6f17a81f6f"><strong>Resellers / Partners</strong> =E2=80=
=93 Reference for client-facing DNS solution deliverables</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"a6ff364ca8cc" id=3D"Task20-Technicaldocument-1.2Scope">1.2 =
Scope</h2>
<p local-id=3D"cbe7be90f375">This document covers the complete implementati=
on of the DNS comparison task assigned to ABC Technologies, including:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"2a3115c11752">Installation and configuration of BIND9 on an =
AWS EC2 instance as a self-hosted authoritative DNS server</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b4a3bb6d9e28">Creation of a DNS zone (lab.karna.pushkar.clou=
d) with A and NS records in BIND9</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"72b9dc073a37">Configuration of AWS Route 53 with NS and glue=
 A records to delegate authority to the self-hosted server</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"ceea29889134">Opening and securing EC2 Security Group port 5=
3 (UDP/TCP) for DNS traffic</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"08af4f96b32f">DNS resolution testing using dig @localhost, d=
ig @EC2-IP, dig NS, and dig +trace</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"2e48fff26c04">Full DNS trace validation confirming the resol=
ution path: Root =E2=86=92 .cloud TLD =E2=86=92 pushkar.cloud (Route 53) =
=E2=86=92 karna.pushkar.cloud (Route 53) =E2=86=92 BIND9 EC2</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h1 local-id=3D"4c8caddb7208" id=3D"Task20-Technicaldocument-2.OverviewofDe=
vOpsProject">2. Overview of DevOps Project</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"0cd56a8aef59" id=3D"Task20-Technicaldocument-2.1Definition"=
>2.1 Definition</h2>
<p local-id=3D"fcbcc547e35f">This project implements a hands-on DNS managem=
ent comparison for ABC Technologies to evaluate the operational and technic=
al differences between a self-hosted DNS solution and a fully managed cloud=
 DNS service. DNS (Domain Name System) is the foundational internet naming =
system that translates human-readable domain names into IP addresses used b=
y servers and network equipment to route traffic.</p>
<p local-id=3D"388f9bbd5947">The exercise demonstrates how authoritative DN=
S control can be shifted between a self-managed BIND9 server running on EC2=
 and AWS Route 53 purely by updating NS (Nameserver) records =E2=80=94 with=
out any change to the underlying application or domain registrar configurat=
ion. This provides ABC Technologies with practical, hands-on insight into D=
NS delegation, propagation behavior, zone file management, and the operatio=
nal complexity trade-off between managing DNS infrastructure versus consumi=
ng it as a managed service.</p>
<h2 local-id=3D"4c269cdc4833" id=3D"Task20-Technicaldocument-2.2KeyPrincipl=
es=E2=80=93AWSWell-ArchitectedFramework">2.2 Key Principles =E2=80=93 AWS W=
ell-Architected Framework</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"1=
81ab1d2-6a7c-4efc-9d3d-751e94c0a5ad" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"ff6dea6ef7c2">Pillar</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"27e6d107032b">Principle</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"8be1d4f65eae">How We Achieved It</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3a652f7e87a3">Operational Excellence</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"82fd21319ab1">Automate and document operational procedures</=
p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c69caa3aa1ee">BIND9 configuration documented as a repeatable=
 step-by-step runbook; dig and nslookup used as validation gates after ever=
y change</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d33e21d8b32a">Security</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"98b5f613e3cc">Apply security at every layer</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"eb425845efdd">EC2 Security Group restricts port 53 (UDP/TCP)=
 access; BIND9 configured as authoritative-only with recursion disabled to =
prevent DNS amplification abuse</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"454ce3404f86">Reliability</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"470131b43608">Ensure systems recover from failures</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"25e944dac0d3">Route 53 provides a 100% SLA-backed managed DN=
S fallback; BIND9 on a single EC2 demonstrates single-node risk; multi-AZ s=
econdary DNS planned as next step</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b4f25e950957">Performance Efficiency</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"45930bd0db33">Use resources efficiently</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"378b822bcdb7">t3.micro EC2 is sufficient for a DNS-only work=
load; Route 53 uses globally distributed Anycast for sub-millisecond resolu=
tion latency</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"0571fb728b97">Cost Optimisation</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3ef4eecb08d3">Avoid unnecessary costs</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"8d8bb3540a54">Route 53 hosted zone at $0.50/month vs a conti=
nuously running EC2 DNS server at ~$9.77/month =E2=80=94 clear TCO comparis=
on provided in Section 8</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f1760dd77ea7">Sustainability</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"98f1ca9bee14">Minimise environmental impact</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"dea0cdfcdc34">Managed Route 53 eliminates idle EC2 compute; =
BIND9 EC2 is decommissioned post-evaluation to avoid unnecessary resource c=
onsumption</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h2 local-id=3D"478dd753b94a" id=3D"Task20-Technicaldocument-2.3GoalsandObj=
ectives">2.3 Goals and Objectives</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b40fd5efa68f">Install and configure BIND9 on an AWS EC2 inst=
ance as a fully functional authoritative DNS server for the zone lab.karna.=
pushkar.cloud</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"fcefa149e7ac">Create DNS records (SOA, NS, A) in the BIND9 z=
one file and validate local resolution using dig @localhost</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"788b3d81ef19">Configure AWS Route 53 with an NS delegation r=
ecord and glue A record to point the lab subdomain to the EC2 BIND9 server<=
/p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"7f65c7db151b">Test and observe DNS resolution using dig and =
dig +trace to confirm the full 5-hop resolution chain</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"8fece689239d">Document the behavior difference between self-=
hosted DNS and Route 53 managed DNS from a resolution, cost, and operationa=
l perspective</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"3a45fecef508">Complete the full implementation and validatio=
n within the 3-hour time constraint</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"ec9f4255ec5a" id=3D"Task20-Technicaldocument-2.4Constraints=
andAssumptions">2.4 Constraints and Assumptions</h2>
<p local-id=3D"30734eca6ef3"><strong>Constraints:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"6d4bee04364e">Budget: Implementation uses a t3.micro EC2 ins=
tance (free tier eligible) and a Route 53 hosted zone ($0.50/month)</p></li=
>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"060e28ae9eb1">Time: Full implementation to be completed with=
in 3 hours</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"a061d3b1b43a">Technology: Stack is fixed =E2=80=94 BIND9, AW=
S EC2 (Ubuntu 24.04), AWS Route 53, domain karna.pushkar.cloud</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"e8a1d2387795">Network: EC2 instance does not have IPv6 enabl=
ed =E2=80=94 IPv6-based DNS resolution falls back to IPv4 automatically (ob=
served in dig +trace output)</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"a7c80827c0eb"><strong>Assumptions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b5c76ce01819">The domain pushkar.cloud is registered and its=
 NS records already delegate karna.pushkar.cloud to Route 53 nameservers (<=
a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"http://ns-482.awsdns-60.com" rel=3D"nofol=
low">ns-482.awsdns-60.com</a>, <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"http://ns=
-984.awsdns-59.net" rel=3D"nofollow">ns-984.awsdns-59.net</a>, <a class=3D"=
external-link" href=3D"http://ns-1234.awsdns-26.org" rel=3D"nofollow">ns-12=
34.awsdns-26.org</a>, <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"http://ns-1637.aws=
dns-12.co.uk" rel=3D"nofollow">ns-1637.awsdns-12.co.uk</a>)</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"0b584c72ef12">The EC2 instance running BIND9 has a known pub=
lic IP: 54.161.204.194</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"a00d9e5cceed">Route 53 hosted zone for karna.pushkar.cloud i=
s active and accessible</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"45da21686b16">The engineer has AWS Console access with permi=
ssions to create Route 53 records and EC2 Security Group rules</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h1 local-id=3D"176a042d6f2b" id=3D"Task20-Technicaldocument-3.Architecture=
andInfrastructure">3. Architecture and Infrastructure</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"2d3590fa2cd6" id=3D"Task20-Technicaldocument-3.1Infrastruct=
ureOverview">3.1 Infrastructure Overview</h2>
<p local-id=3D"d3c285b5e033">The solution involves two parallel DNS environ=
ments serving the same subdomain (lab.karna.pushkar.cloud), with authority =
delegated from Route 53 to the self-hosted BIND9 EC2 server via an NS recor=
d and a glue A record:</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"0=
f45ec08-8ac6-4fda-b9af-83f14e4ac4ca" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 364.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 500.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 934.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"47a8b470e8aa">Layer</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"eaeb3b5481ce">Component</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"2ffed091cb59">Detail</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"5aa5a1bd7bf1">DNS Server (Self-Hosted)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"2c69501eb948">EC2 =E2=80=93 BIND9</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"84e4c58ec92b">ubuntu@ip-172-31-92-210 | Public IP: 54.161.20=
4.194 | BIND9 authoritative DNS</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"8ca20d36666f">Zone (Self-Hosted)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d33ed21d866d">lab.karna.pushkar.cloud</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f8ef6fdb6923">Hosted in /etc/bind/db.lab.karna.pushkar.cloud=
 on EC2</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4c6ce0c5b7fa">DNS Service (Managed)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"72e7a650fed2">AWS Route 53</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f7f4ce48eea3">Hosted Zone: karna.pushkar.cloud | Delegates l=
ab subdomain to EC2</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"9f50c40df310">NS Delegation Record</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"eb6e9f71ceef">Route 53 NS Record</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a6b724aa8dc1">lab.karna.pushkar.cloud =E2=86=92 ns1.lab.karn=
a.pushkar.cloud</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"237c2bd0ebec">Glue A Record</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"5b31291dcf5d">Route 53 A Record</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c9deea3b36fc">ns1.lab.karna.pushkar.cloud =E2=86=92 54.161.2=
04.194</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3f1cad1c20ce">Parent Zone</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b61b45c80d6c">pushkar.cloud (Route 53)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"de8457b773f2">Delegates karna.pushkar.cloud to Route 53 host=
ed zone NS servers</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d5fdb306c059">Domain Registrar</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"922e82c6f509">.cloud TLD Registry</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f6d9570a3620">Delegates pushkar.cloud to Route 53 via TLD NS=
 records</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"107bc586eb23">Testing Tools</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"bf95acc2df6f">dig / nslookup</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b27e5813cb16">Used for local, external, and full trace-based=
 DNS validation</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h2 local-id=3D"4a7285492d3f" id=3D"Task20-Technicaldocument-3.2Environment=
s">3.2 Environments</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"e=
442c2f1-8910-4398-9229-f06f4cda4858" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"486e5fce8cc9">Environment</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"e8d98f70c992">Status</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"c9b59561cff1">Description</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c749f461d161">Self-Hosted DNS</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"04ab1c356752">Active (EC2)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"0424b7415111">BIND9 running on EC2 (54.161.204.194), authori=
tative for lab.karna.pushkar.cloud, responding on port 53 UDP/TCP</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"480cd2db8f56">Route 53 Managed DNS</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f6741625f14e">Active</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"19db48b9a095">Hosted zone karna.pushkar.cloud; NS record del=
egates lab subdomain to the EC2 BIND9 server</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"25b40d6ec27a">Testing Environment</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a892cab1b3a2">EC2 Shell</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3ee0dfa35ca7">dig commands run from ubuntu@ip-172-31-92-210 =
to validate local, external, and traced resolution</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h2 local-id=3D"3c84b995d65e" id=3D"Task20-Technicaldocument-3.3Application=
Architecture&amp;UserRequestFlow">3.3 Application Architecture &amp; User R=
equest Flow</h2>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">User DN=
S Query: lab.karna.pushkar.cloud
              =E2=86=93
  Root DNS Servers (.)
  j.root-servers.net, f.root-servers.net, m.root-servers.net, etc.
              =E2=86=93
  .cloud TLD Nameservers
  ns01.trs-dns.com / ns01.trs-dns.net / ns10.trs-dns.org / ns10.trs-dns.inf=
o
              =E2=86=93
  pushkar.cloud Nameservers (Route 53)
  ns-482.awsdns-60.com   ns-984.awsdns-59.net
  ns-1234.awsdns-26.org  ns-1637.awsdns-12.co.uk
              =E2=86=93
  karna.pushkar.cloud Nameservers (Route 53)
  ns-1475.awsdns-56.org  ns-1593.awsdns-07.co.uk
  ns-315.awsdns-39.com   ns-866.awsdns-44.net
              =E2=86=93
  NS Record: lab.karna.pushkar.cloud =E2=86=92 ns1.lab.karna.pushkar.cloud
  Glue A Record: ns1.lab.karna.pushkar.cloud =E2=86=92 54.161.204.194
              =E2=86=93
  Self-Hosted BIND9 DNS Server (EC2: 54.161.204.194:53)
              =E2=86=93
  Authoritative Answer: lab.karna.pushkar.cloud IN A 54.161.204.194</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"8289ab026989">The DNS resolution path traverses five hops: R=
oot Servers =E2=86=92 .cloud TLD =E2=86=92 pushkar.cloud (Route 53) =E2=86=
=92 karna.pushkar.cloud (Route 53) =E2=86=92 EC2 BIND9 authoritative answer=
. The NS record in Route 53 and the glue A record are the two critical reco=
rds that hand off authority from the managed Route 53 layer to the self-hos=
ted BIND9 server. Without the glue A record, resolvers cannot find the IP o=
f ns1.lab.karna.pushkar.cloud and resolution breaks with a circular depende=
ncy.</p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrappe=
r confluence-embedded-manual-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image =
image-center" alt=3D"image (11)-20260322-122019.png" width=3D"468" loading=
=3D"lazy" src=3D"61ee5b336b9b61934f1e68716eea1a785ffe1766a0b60d63104e39d456=
443973" data-image-src=3D"https://iamops.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attach=
ments/1885667783/image%20(11)-20260322-122019.png?version=3D1&amp;modificat=
ionDate=3D1774182079913&amp;cacheVersion=3D1&amp;api=3Dv2" data-height=3D"2=
716" data-width=3D"1474" data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-re=
source-id=3D"1887043853" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-res=
ource-type=3D"attachment" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image (11)-=
20260322-122019.png" data-base-url=3D"https://iamops.atlassian.net/wiki" da=
ta-linked-resource-content-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-containe=
r-id=3D"1885667783" data-linked-resource-container-version=3D"2" data-media=
-id=3D"7133d8b2-f07d-495c-b0bb-23947bb4f0f3" data-media-type=3D"file" heigh=
t=3D"860"></span>
<p local-id=3D"8d16681976d5"></p>
