<h1 local-id=3D"2d8f473c06d1" id=3D"Task20-Technicaldocument-4.DevelopmentP=
ractices">4. Development Practices</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"9df8a203b86b" id=3D"Task20-Technicaldocument-4.1VersionCont=
rol">4.1 Version Control</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"6ebcb5f9b908">All BIND9 configuration files (named.conf.loca=
l and zone data files) are version-controlled in a GitHub repository as inf=
rastructure configuration =E2=80=94 enabling rollback and change tracking</=
p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"5e4e07b0219b">Zone file changes follow a branch-based workfl=
ow: modifications are made on a feature branch, reviewed for correctness (S=
OA serial increment, record syntax), and merged to main before being applie=
d to the EC2 server</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"179f6d2121ec">The SOA serial number in the zone file is incr=
emented on every change (format: YYYYMMDDNN) to signal secondary resolvers =
and caching DNS servers that the zone has been updated</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"bdae65a6bc5f">Route 53 record changes are automatically logg=
ed in AWS CloudTrail =E2=80=94 providing a complete, immutable audit trail =
of all DNS record additions, modifications, and deletions with timestamps a=
nd IAM identity</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"646c81b79dcb" id=3D"Task20-Technicaldocument-4.2ContinuousI=
ntegration">4.2 Continuous Integration</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"7a1cdf18612f">For this implementation, CI is achieved throug=
h a manual validation gate: after every BIND9 configuration change, named-c=
heckconf and named-checkzone are run to validate syntax before the service =
is restarted</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"12a9f0933b27">Route 53 record changes are immediately valida=
ted via dig queries against the Route 53 nameservers =E2=80=94 providing ne=
ar-instant feedback on record propagation</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"3e8c6f314f3e">Future enhancement: A GitHub Actions workflow =
can run named-checkzone on every zone file pull request and automatically a=
pply approved changes to the EC2 BIND9 server via Ansible or AWS SSM Run Co=
mmand on merge to main</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"a9b9307a187d" id=3D"Task20-Technicaldocument-4.3AutomatedTe=
sting">4.3 Automated Testing</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"19a3bf4a41ce">DNS resolution is tested at three levels after=
 every configuration change: local (dig @localhost), external (dig @54.161.=
204.194), and full-chain (dig +trace)</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"342a58385606">dig +trace serves as an end-to-end integration=
 test =E2=80=94 it confirms the complete resolution chain from root servers=
 through TLD, Route 53, and finally to the BIND9 authoritative answer</p></=
li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b529a6e58056">The ANSWER SECTION in dig output is used as th=
e pass/fail assertion: presence of lab.karna.pushkar.cloud. IN A 54.161.204=
.194 confirms a successful resolution</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"9066507010b4">Future: Automated synthetic monitoring using a=
 cron job that runs dig @54.161.204.194 lab.karna.pushkar.cloud every 60 se=
conds and alerts if no ANSWER SECTION is returned</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"9cf20b5e8ff6" id=3D"Task20-Technicaldocument-4.4CodeQuality=
andAnalysis">4.4 Code Quality and Analysis</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"ddb3e552a719">BIND9 zone files are validated using named-che=
ckzone before every service restart to catch misconfigurations that would c=
ause silent resolution failures</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"048bd0f77748">named.conf syntax is validated using named-che=
ckconf =E2=80=94 a single syntax error in this file prevents BIND9 from sta=
rting entirely</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"75ff45d52d49">TTL values are set deliberately: 604800 (7 day=
s) for stable production A records; lower values (300 seconds) used during =
initial setup to accelerate propagation observation and reduce testing cycl=
e time</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"57f63ff157b2">Zone serial numbers are tracked and always inc=
remented on every change =E2=80=94 skipping this step is one of the most co=
mmon causes of DNS caching issues where changes appear to have no effect</p=
></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h1 local-id=3D"97c4f3edbab3" id=3D"Task20-Technicaldocument-5.Deploymentan=
dReleaseManagement">5. Deployment and Release Management</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"5e66f0f6f866" id=3D"Task20-Technicaldocument-5.1DeploymentS=
trategy">5.1 Deployment Strategy</h2>
<p local-id=3D"ee775c59db84">DNS configuration changes follow a staged depl=
oyment approach with validation gates between each stage to prevent resolut=
ion outages:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"1ba03ee07854"><strong>Stage 1 =E2=80=93 Syntax Validation:</=
strong> All BIND9 zone file changes are validated locally using named-check=
zone before applying to the live server</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"0301ae749a89"><strong>Stage 2 =E2=80=93 Service Restart:</st=
rong> bind9 is restarted via systemctl and service status is verified =E2=
=80=94 Active: active (running) is the required state before proceeding</p>=
</li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"65dc0a1d2099"><strong>Stage 3 =E2=80=93 Local Resolution Tes=
t:</strong> dig @localhost confirms the BIND9 server responds correctly wit=
h the expected A record before any external exposure</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"76af2891f71f"><strong>Stage 4 =E2=80=93 External Resolution =
Test:</strong> dig @54.161.204.194 from an external machine confirms port 5=
3 is open and the server is reachable from the internet</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"5fe4361bb624"><strong>Stage 5 =E2=80=93 NS Delegation:</stro=
ng> NS and glue A records are added to Route 53 only after BIND9 is confirm=
ed working =E2=80=94 this prevents a broken delegation state where the NS r=
ecord points to a non-functional server</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"dde3170dc259"><strong>Stage 6 =E2=80=93 Full Trace Validatio=
n:</strong> dig +trace confirms the complete global resolution chain termin=
ates at the BIND9 EC2 server</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"0470d6811f51" id=3D"Task20-Technicaldocument-5.2Configurati=
onManagement">5.2 Configuration Management</h2>
<p local-id=3D"47e8065de4b9"><strong>BIND9 Zone Declaration (/etc/bind/name=
d.conf.local):</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">zone "l=
ab.karna.pushkar.cloud" {
    type master;
    file "/etc/bind/db.lab.karna.pushkar.cloud";
};</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"63976dc13be6"><strong>Zone Data File (/etc/bind/db.lab.karna=
.pushkar.cloud):</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">$TTL   =
 604800
@   IN  SOA  ns1.lab.karna.pushkar.cloud. admin.lab.karna.pushkar.cloud. (
                  2         ; Serial
             604800         ; Refresh
              86400         ; Retry
            2419200         ; Expire
             604800 )       ; Negative Cache TTL
;
@   IN  NS   ns1.lab.karna.pushkar.cloud.
@   IN  A    54.161.204.194
ns1 IN  A    54.161.204.194</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"3145a79ae93a"><strong>Route 53 Records Added in karna.pushka=
r.cloud Hosted Zone:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"6=
21909e2-d29d-4f1d-be8f-bb4f8bdda7ed" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"2d12cbef0aff">Record Name</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"6277125c94e3">Type</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"a4c34a214cc5">Value</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"7d271ccb34cc">Purpose</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"8d6d6125fc31">lab.karna.pushkar.cloud</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"6db6397fad40">NS</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"8254f000bf94">ns1.lab.karna.pushkar.cloud</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d9c5d63310b9">Delegates lab subdomain to self-hosted BIND9</=
p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3193db749bb2">ns1.lab.karna.pushkar.cloud</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3db5c68f22ee">A</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"fa13e274f191">54.161.204.194</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f23faa4f7038">Glue record =E2=80=94 resolves nameserver host=
name to IP</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h2 local-id=3D"237c55b4f597" id=3D"Task20-Technicaldocument-5.3ContinuousD=
elivery/Deployment">5.3 Continuous Delivery / Deployment</h2>
<p local-id=3D"04bb43b8269b">The complete step-by-step deployment workflow =
from EC2 provisioning to validated DNS resolution:</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"f=
c1957e0-3f2a-4d07-bba1-d3087505a36d" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"798b3e6520c7">Step</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"2fe673f642e9">Action</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"5c7e538843cb">Command / Detail</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"66909decaf84">1</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"7daeb975fb2f">Update package index and install BIND9</p></td=
>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c01f5711194e">sudo apt update &amp;&amp; sudo apt install bi=
nd9 -y</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ab6beba04ce7">2</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"90cd021028d9">Open zone declaration config</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"19d27b3e2741">sudo nano /etc/bind/named.conf.local</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4e59650ded97">3</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"160b0aa6ec43">Add zone block for lab.karna.pushkar.cloud</p>=
</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3b4b1eba328f">type master; file /etc/bind/db.lab.karna.pushk=
ar.cloud;</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"dc1c0c2743a4">4</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"809159a92ad8">Copy default zone file as template</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"cc8ed9402c26">sudo cp /etc/bind/db.local /etc/bind/db.lab.ka=
rna.pushkar.cloud</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"9499ff008322">5</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"94c1bf2e6a0e">Edit zone data file</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b1efef746b0e">sudo nano /etc/bind/db.lab.karna.pushkar.cloud=
 =E2=80=94 add SOA, NS, A records</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"0d50d741bfc9">6</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"98c694ac4f51">Open port 53 in EC2 Security Group</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"da7d89b64357">Add UDP/TCP port 53 inbound rules =E2=80=94 So=
urce: 0.0.0.0/0</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c1fa7b8d8a3f">7</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"810636ac2387">Restart BIND9 and verify status</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4c4346d4e96c">sudo systemctl restart bind9 &amp;&amp; sudo s=
ystemctl status bind9</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"25715a437c2f">8</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b7ac6e8b8971">Test local resolution</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4fb0ce5e21d4">dig @localhost lab.karna.pushkar.cloud</p></td=
>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d2aa487019c3">9</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"68c1f6a28ba7">Test external resolution</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"8730bd632459">dig @54.161.204.194 lab.karna.pushkar.cloud</p=
></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"17a8887df1e9">10</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4aa7fb527632">Add NS + Glue A records in Route 53</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"39ee639c9ad0">NS: lab =E2=86=92 ns1.lab; A: ns1.lab =E2=86=
=92 54.161.204.194</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f788f20f4ab9">11</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3e70a2fe6351">Verify NS delegation</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"52618e150edb">dig NS lab.karna.pushkar.cloud</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b6793237538a">12</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"576e54c09a89">Full trace validation</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d1a2bbcc0d65">dig +trace lab.karna.pushkar.cloud</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"35a2978826c0">13</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"0c85555d5f1b">Confirm final answer source</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a0eb4480b3c1">Final answer received from 54.161.204.194 (BIN=
D9 EC2)</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<h1 local-id=3D"271aaa579223" id=3D"Task20-Technicaldocument-6.Monitoringan=
dIncidentManagement">6. Monitoring and Incident Management</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"ef8cad26ff70" id=3D"Task20-Technicaldocument-6.1MonitoringT=
oolsandMetrics">6.1 Monitoring Tools and Metrics</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"1894a5e7ea8f"><strong>systemctl status bind9:</strong> Real-=
time service health =E2=80=94 confirms Active: active (running) after every=
 restart or configuration change</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"c237b423cee4"><strong>dig @localhost:</strong> Local resolut=
ion test =E2=80=94 used as the first validation check after every BIND9 con=
figuration change</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"bf62904c3bad"><strong>dig +trace:</strong> Full resolution p=
ath trace =E2=80=94 validates the entire DNS delegation chain from root ser=
vers to the authoritative BIND9 answer; used as the final validation gate</=
p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"5e0d1e42d380"><strong>BIND9 System Log (/var/log/syslog):</s=
trong> BIND9 logs all queries, zone load events, configuration errors, and =
service lifecycle events to syslog =E2=80=94 primary source for debugging r=
esolution failures</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"acb36caf74b0"><strong>AWS Route 53 Health Checks:</strong> C=
an be configured to monitor port 53 on the BIND9 EC2 instance and trigger a=
lerts if the DNS server stops responding</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"1e1ebb9a98b6"><strong>AWS CloudTrail:</strong> Logs all Rout=
e 53 API calls =E2=80=94 provides a complete audit trail for NS record addi=
tions, modifications, and deletions</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"cda4c5e6debf" id=3D"Task20-Technicaldocument-6.2Alertingand=
Notification">6.2 Alerting and Notification</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"954c8b418440"><strong>BIND9 Service Crash:</strong> systemd =
OnFailure=3D directive can trigger an alert script or SNS notification if b=
ind9.service enters a failed state</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"84870e1ec1d7"><strong>Route 53 Health Check Alarm:</strong> =
CloudWatch alarm on the Route 53 health check failure metric =E2=86=92 SNS =
email/Slack notification to the DNS operations team</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"74efafab31aa"><strong>EC2 Instance Down:</strong> CloudWatch=
 alarm on EC2 StatusCheckFailed_Instance =E2=86=92 alerts if the BIND9 host=
 becomes unreachable</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"9cac9213066e"><strong>Resolution Failure Detection:</strong>=
 Cron job running dig @54.161.204.194 lab.karna.pushkar.cloud every 60 seco=
nds =E2=80=94 logs failures and triggers an alert if ANSWER SECTION is abse=
nt from the response</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"a30ca61beaca" id=3D"Task20-Technicaldocument-6.3IncidentMan=
agement">6.3 Incident Management</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"4=
74107ab-084d-4692-be96-f8d6cd8eaa8e" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"6aaab8e3b393">Severity</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"ef856ea782b5">Example</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"ab4626936c04">Response</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"cc513443c8a9">Resolution Target</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"2323a1c8236a">P1 =E2=80=93 Critical</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"12061751905f">BIND9 down, all DNS queries failing</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"0836a0481f62">Immediately run systemctl restart bind9; check=
 /var/log/syslog for errors; if EC2 unreachable, update Route 53 NS record =
to point to Route 53 A record as emergency fallback</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a91014df8c4f">&lt; 15 minutes</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"24bcb4f2f4b8">P2 =E2=80=93 High</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"5f15c0ffbc6c">Port 53 blocked, external queries timing out</=
p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"5d3a0cc497b7">Review EC2 Security Group inbound rules; verif=
y UDP/TCP port 53 rules exist; test with dig @54.161.204.194 after fix</p><=
/td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"362824aa13e5">&lt; 30 minutes</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d45bd1f2c0bf">P3 =E2=80=93 Medium</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"8c9f4bd07636">Zone file syntax error after update</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"10dc2c2fe1a3">Run named-checkzone to identify the error; fix=
 zone file; increment SOA serial; restart bind9; validate with dig @localho=
st</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"2659c1819ad9">&lt; 1 hour</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"0801defbd763">P4 =E2=80=93 Low</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3a74131e9213">DNS propagation delay after NS change</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"564db1abc299">Wait for TTL expiry (300s for Route 53 NS reco=
rds); use dig +trace to monitor live propagation status; no action required=
 if resolution eventually succeeds</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"5bebc695728e">TTL-dependent</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<h1 local-id=3D"029aa30f1b13" id=3D"Task20-Technicaldocument-7.Security&amp=
;Compliance">7. Security &amp; Compliance</h1>
<p local-id=3D"5aa86b5f07f2"><strong>Infrastructure Security:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"1ae3d9e6da40"><strong>Port 53 Scope:</strong> During testing=
, EC2 Security Group allows port 53 (UDP/TCP) from 0.0.0.0/0 to enable exte=
rnal dig validation; in production this should be scoped to known resolver =
IPs or the VPC CIDR to limit exposure</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"69bdc2a26644"><strong>Authoritative-Only Mode:</strong> BIND=
9 is configured as an authoritative DNS server with recursion disabled (rec=
ursion no;) =E2=80=94 this prevents the server from acting as an open recur=
sive resolver, which is a common vector for DNS amplification DDoS attacks<=
/p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"725d174e20f3"><strong>Zone Transfer Restriction:</strong> al=
low-transfer { none; }; is set in the BIND9 configuration =E2=80=94 prevent=
s unauthorized secondary DNS servers from copying the zone data</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"bfb9f69c4884"><strong>No Open SSH:</strong> EC2 port 22 is r=
estricted to the administrator's IP in the Security Group =E2=80=94 all oth=
er inbound ports are denied by default</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"986de13d0a9b"><strong>Route 53 IAM Restriction:</strong> NS =
and A record creation in Route 53 requires the IAM permission route53:Chang=
eResourceRecordSets, scoped to the specific hosted zone ARN =E2=80=94 not a=
ccount-wide admin access</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"204d541456c0"><strong>Identity and Access Management (IAM):<=
/strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"6d91627bd480"><strong>EC2 IAM Role:</strong> The EC2 instanc=
e running BIND9 has a minimal IAM role =E2=80=94 no Route 53 permissions ar=
e assigned to the DNS server itself, enforcing separation of concerns betwe=
en the DNS serving plane and the DNS management plane</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"c741d6102d07"><strong>Route 53 Management Role:</strong> DNS=
 record changes are performed by a separate IAM role with route53:ChangeRes=
ourceRecordSets permission scoped to the karna.pushkar.cloud hosted zone on=
ly =E2=80=94 preventing accidental or malicious modification of other hoste=
d zones</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"12167f867e02"><strong>Least Privilege Enforcement:</strong> =
No AWS admin keys are stored on the EC2 BIND9 instance; all Route 53 manage=
ment operations are performed from a secured workstation via the AWS Consol=
e or CLI</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"27b34ad46f8d"><strong>CloudTrail Audit Trail:</strong> All R=
oute 53 API calls =E2=80=94 including NS record creation, modification, and=
 deletion =E2=80=94 are logged in CloudTrail with full IAM identity, timest=
amp, and source IP for compliance and forensic review</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h1 local-id=3D"84f946b521a1" id=3D"Task20-Technicaldocument-8.CostOptimisa=
tion">8. Cost Optimisation</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"ae40fe89b21e" id=3D"Task20-Technicaldocument-TotalCostofOwn=
ership(TCO)Analysis">Total Cost of Ownership (TCO) Analysis</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
